				<div class="postbody">
				This is why the US has a system of checks and balances.  Perfection is impossible.  Any system can be abused and any system can and will make mistakes.  This, of course, is the best argument against the death penalty, as that's one sentence that can't be appealed once it's carried out.  You can never give people years of their life back, but you can at least release them from prison.
<br />

<br />
No ratio of abuse is truly "acceptable"; society must always work at purging abuse and injustice from the system.  Hence the value of our rights of free speech, free press and (when all else fails) the right to bear arms.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
