<br />

<br />
Programs such as post secondary education, where you have to buy "useless" credits such as speech, gym or language. My time and effort could be spent better else, where learning to specialize in the profession of my choice with more hands on work such as an internship/volunteer work. The true onset of adulthood is comming later and later in society from  the added requirements of "you must go to college" and get a "well rounded education." The faster someone is put to work, less debt/work needed for education, and the more money a person would have for their Healthcare.
<br />

<br />
Society just needs to cut out the extra crap, and get back to the basics. Less time spent on fluff from idealists the better, and more time spent on the neccissities of life and we'd be better off. Offering programs for better education that allow people to sustain a better living condition okay(mostly paid through private donations/lottery-like programs), but if they're not going to work its time to just let them die/suffer. This isn't Utopia, its real life.<br />
