			<tr><td colspan="2"><hr /></td></tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				You asked how it can be that healthcare is proportionally more expensive now than it was 30 years ago, and there's your answer.  More and more procedures and prescriptions are being covered under our health care system these days, which means a substantial rise in its cost.  
<br />

<br />
Again, do I believe that everything that is covered is necessary?  Hell no.  But the system as a whole works, and there aren't really alot of changes that need to be made to it at this point.  
<br />

<br />
In response to the whole spiralling out of control aspect of it, I totally agree with you poppa.  Someone has to start putting stricter limits on usage so the system doesn't deteriorate any further.  More money doesnt equal better health care.  The cash needs to be spent efficiently in order to make an impact. 
<br />

<br />
Meletus v1.0
<br />
Retired 65 dr00d<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
