			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Elberich is correct.  The biggest problems in the Canadian health care system right now are the waits for surgery and cancer treatments.  These big ticket items are in demand with the aging population and the fact that the US is currently paying more for doctors with qualifications in these areas.
<br />

<br />
For most health care needs, you can see your doctor quickly or just go to a walk in clinic. 
<br />

<br />
Does anyone have any cost comparisons for the US and Canada for health care?  Some kind of average cost per person covered, perhaps?  It will be difficult to do comparisons with a level playing field due to the differences in how the two systems operate, but it's more fun having numbers to crunch and consider than bare philosophical arguments.
<br />

<br />
Much &lt;3 Poppa.  Say hi to the Mrs for me.<br />
